 certificate requirements\n- The base ContextImpl class (source/common/tls/context_impl.cc) initializes SSL contexts through cert_validator_->initializeSslContexts(), which returns verification mode flags\n- Custom verification callbacks are registered via SSL_CTX_set_custom_verify() on line 181 to handle asynchronous validation\n\n**Key Verification Infrastructure:**\n- CertValidator abstract interface (source/common/tls/cert_validator/cert_validator.h) defines the contract for all validators\n- The verification modes are determined by the initializeSslContexts() methods and returned as int flags (SSL_VERIFY_NONE, SSL_VERIFY_PEER, SSL_VERIFY_FAIL_IF_NO_PEER_CERT)\n- Error handling and verification result tracking occurs through ValidationResults structures and detailed_status enums\n- Utility functions in source/common/tls/utility.cc provide error reporting and certificate information extraction\n\nThe architecture allows for both synchronous and asynchronous certificate verification, with support for multiple validation strategies (trust anchor validation, certificate pinning, SPIFFE-specific validation) and comprehensive error handling and logging."
